                "institute": "1USAORL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment was performed at the",
                "Holifield Radioactive Ion Beam Facility at Oak Ridge",
                "National Laboratory using Low-Energy Radioactive Ion",
                "Beam Spectroscopy Station (LeRIBSS)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "31-GA-86",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 1.0
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Ions of 86Ga were extracted from",
                "the Resonant Ionization Laser Ion Source (RILIS),",
                "utilizing a two-step ionization scheme, accelerated",
                "to 200 keV kinetic energy, and mass analyzed by a",
                "two-stage mass separator having mass resolving powers",
                "M/dM of 1000 and 10 000, respectively.The beam was",
                "implanted into the moving tape collector. Tape",
                "collector periodically transported implanted ions to",
                "the detector setup center."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Beta rays were detected by two plastic beta",
                " ray detectors"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Gamma rays were detected using two high-purity",
                "germanium clover detectors"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HE3SP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were detected using 48 3He",
                "ionization chambers. The neutron counters, containing",
                "in total about 600 liters of 3He, were mounted in a",
                "thermalizing high-density polyethylene (HDPE) support",
                "with a 1-mm-thick cadmium outer shielding."
              ]
            }
          ],
